y Vizio (Add or remove brands as your content grows.)\nLatest Additions # Here are some of the newest pages added to the site:\nCheck the Devices section for the most recently added error codes:\n👉 View All Devices\nWhy This Site Exists # Error codes can be confusing — especially when manuals are vague or missing. Error Code Hub was created to provide:\nclear explanations of what each code means real‑world symptoms you might see common causes based on technician experience safe, practical fixes anyone can follow model‑specific notes when brands reuse codes This helps you diagnose problems faster and decide whether you can fix the issue yourself or need a technician.\nHow to Use This Site # Search for your brand + device + error code Read the meaning and symptoms Follow the step‑by‑step fixes Review safety notes before attempting repairs Check the applicable models list to confirm accuracy Disclaimer # This site is for informational purposes only. Electrical and mechanical repairs involve risk. Always follow manufacturer instructions and consider contacting a qualified technician for diagnosis or repair.\n","externalUrl":null,"permalink":"/error-code-hub/","section":"Error Code Hub","summary":"A complete database of appliance, TV, computer, and phone error codes — organized by brand, device type, and model.","title":"Error Code Hub","type":"error-code-hub"},{"content":"","externalUrl":null,"permalink":"/error-code-hub/devices/appliances/washer/maytag/","section":"Error Code Hub","summary":"","title":"Maytag Washer Error Codes","type":"section"},{"content":" Welcome to Minted Tools # Minted Tools is a collection of free, practical, no‑nonsense tools designed to help people solve real‑world problems. Each project is built to be fast, lightweight, and easy to use — with no sign‑ups, no paywalls, and no clutter.\nOur goal is simple:\nCreate tools that save time, reduce frustration, and deliver clear answers.\nFeatured Project: Error Code Hub # Error Code Hub →\nError Code Hub is a growing database of appliance, TV, computer, and phone error codes, organized by:\ndevice type brand model error code Each page includes:\nwhat the error code means symptoms you may notice common causes step‑by‑step fixes safety notes applicable models If you\u0026rsquo;re troubleshooting a washer, diagnosing a refrigerator, or trying to understand a TV or laptop error, Error Code Hub gives you clear explanations without the confusing technical jargon.\nWhat Minted Tools Offers # Minted Tools is built around three core principles:\n1. Practical Tools # Every project solves a real problem — whether it’s troubleshooting, diagnostics, organization, or automation.\n2. Clean, Fast, Lightweight Design # No ads (unless required for monetization), no bloat, no distractions.\nJust fast, useful tools that load instantly.\n3. Built to Scale # Each tool is designed to grow over time, with new features, categories, and improvements added regularly.\nCurrent Projects # 🔧 Error Code Hub # A complete database of appliance, TV, computer, and phone error codes.\n👉 Visit: Error Code Hub\nUpcoming Tools # Minted Tools will expand with additional utilities, including:\ntroubleshooting assistants diagnostic checklists home maintenance tools tech reference guides calculators and workflow helpers As new tools launch, they will appear here on the homepage.\nAbout Minted Tools # Minted Tools is built with:\nHugo for speed Blowfish for clean design GitHub Pages for reliability modular architecture for easy expansion Every project is designed to be:\nfast mobile‑friendly accessible SEO‑optimized easy to maintain Stay Updated # New tools and updates are added regularly.\nBookmark this page and check back as the Minted Tools ecosystem grows.\n","externalUrl":null,"permalink":"/","section":"Minted Tools","summary":"Minted Tools is a hub for practical, free tools and resources — starting with Error Code Hub.","title":"Minted Tools","type":"page"},{"content":"","externalUrl":null,"permal